    {id:'log-analytics',title:'Log Analytics Workspace',tag:'Monitoring',summary:'Centralized log storage and analysis with KQL querying.',definition:'Log Analytics Workspace is a centralized repository for log data with powerful querying and analysis capabilities.',what:'Workspace stores and analyzes logs from resources, with KQL query language support.',why:'It enables troubleshooting, performance analysis, and compliance logging.',analogy:'Like a centralized library where you can search through all your logs and analyze patterns.',hindi:'Log Analytics logs ko store aur analyze karta hai. KQL queries use karke powerful analysis ho sakta hai.',terraform:'azurerm_log_analytics_workspace',example:'resource "azurerm_log_analytics_workspace" "main" { name = "law-prod" sku = "PerGB2018" }',practices:'Enable archive storage, implement data retention policies, use saved queries.',mistakes:'No retention policy, expensive queries, not archiving old data.',production:'30-day hot retention, archive after 30 days, solution packs deployed.',learnUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-monitor/logs/log-analytics-overview',terraformUrl:'https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/azurerm/latest/docs/resources/log_analytics_workspace',youtubeUrl:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=azure+log+analytics',githubUrl:'https://github.com/search?q=azure+log+analytics+terraform',docsUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-monitor/logs/'},
    {id:'app-insights',title:'Application Insights',tag:'Monitoring',summary:'Application performance monitoring and diagnostics.',definition:'Application Insights is an application performance monitoring service that provides diagnostics and performance insights.',what:'Application Insights monitors application health with request tracking, performance metrics, and custom events.',why:'It enables application troubleshooting, performance optimization, and user behavior analysis.',analogy:'Like having a personal assistant that watches your application health and alerts you to issues.',hindi:'Application Insights application performance track karta hai. Errors aur slow requests identify karta hai.',terraform:'azurerm_application_insights',example:'resource "azurerm_application_insights" "main" { name = "ai-prod" application_type = "web" }',practices:'Use sampling in production, implement custom events, track user flows.',mistakes:'No sampling causing high costs, not implementing custom tracking.',production:'Fixed-rate sampling at 10%, custom events for business metrics.',learnUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-monitor/app/app-insights-overview',terraformUrl:'https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/azurerm/latest/docs/resources/application_insights',youtubeUrl:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=azure+application+insights',githubUrl:'https://github.com/search?q=azure+application+insights+terraform',docsUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-monitor/app/'},
    {id:'backup-vault',title:'Recovery Services Vault',tag:'Backup',summary:'Backup and disaster recovery for Azure resources.',definition:'Recovery Services Vault is a centralized service for backing up and recovering Azure resources.',what:'Vault stores backups and enables disaster recovery for VMs, databases, and on-premises servers.',why:'It provides centralized backup management, supports long-term retention, enables business continuity.',analogy:'Like an insurance policy that keeps your backups safe and helps restore after disasters.',hindi:'Recovery Services Vault backup store karta hai. Disaster recovery aur long-term retention provide karta hai.',terraform:'azurerm_recovery_services_vault',example:'resource "azurerm_recovery_services_vault" "main" { name = "rsv-prod" sku = "Standard" }',practices:'Enable soft delete, configure backup policies, test restore procedures.',mistakes:'Not testing restores, poor retention policies, not enabling redundancy.',production:'GRS redundancy, soft delete enabled, regular restore tests, automated backup policies.',learnUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/backup/backup-overview',terraformUrl:'https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/azurerm/latest/docs/resources/recovery_services_vault',youtubeUrl:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=azure+recovery+services+vault',githubUrl:'https://github.com/search?q=azure+recovery+services+terraform',docsUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/backup/'},
    {id:'vm-scale-set',title:'VM Scale Set',tag:'Compute',summary:'Auto-scaling group of identical VMs for high availability.',definition:'Virtual Machine Scale Set creates and manages a group of load-balanced VMs with automatic scaling.',what:'Scale Set automatically scales VMs based on demand with load balancer integration.',why:'It simplifies scaling, provides high availability, reduces deployment time.',analogy:'Like having a manager who hires or fires workers based on how busy the restaurant is.',hindi:'VM Scale Set identical VMs ka managed group provide karta hai. Auto-scaling support karta hai.',terraform:'azurerm_linux_virtual_machine_scale_set',example:'resource "azurerm_linux_virtual_machine_scale_set" "main" { name = "vmss-prod" sku = "Standard_D2s_v3" }',practices:'Use managed disks, implement health probes, configure autoscaling policies.',mistakes:'No autoscaling configured, ignoring health probes, uneven load distribution.',production:'Health probes enabled, autoscaling on metrics, managed identity configured.',learnUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machine-scale-sets/overview',terraformUrl:'https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/azurerm/latest/docs/resources/linux_virtual_machine_scale_set',youtubeUrl:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=azure+vm+scale+set',githubUrl:'https://github.com/search?q=azure+scale+set+terraform',docsUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machine-scale-sets/'},
    {id:'availability-set',title:'Availability Set',tag:'Compute',summary:'Logical grouping for high availability of VMs.',definition:'Availability Set ensures VMs are distributed across fault domains and update domains for resilience.',what:'Availability Set places VMs in separate fault and update domains to minimize downtime.',why:'It provides redundancy against hardware failures and planned maintenance.',analogy:'Like putting backup servers in different physical locations so one failure does not take all down.',hindi:'Availability Set VMs ko different fault domains mein distribute karta hai. High availability ensure karta hai.',terraform:'azurerm_availability_set',example:'resource "azurerm_availability_set" "main" { name = "avset-prod" platform_fault_domain_count = 3 }',practices:'Use 2-3 VMs minimum, configure with Load Balancer, not required with zones.',mistakes:'Single VM in availability set, combining with availability zones incorrectly.',production:'Minimum 2 VMs, load balanced, or use availability zones instead.',learnUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machines/availability-set-overview',terraformUrl:'https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/azurerm/latest/docs/resources/availability_set',youtubeUrl:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=azure+availability+set',githubUrl:'https://github.com/search?q=azure+availability+set+terraform',docsUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machines/availability-set-overview'},
    {id:'availability-zone',title:'Availability Zone',tag:'Compute',summary:'Isolated data centers within an Azure region for fault tolerance.',definition:'Availability Zones are isolated physical locations within an Azure region for fault isolation.',what:'Availability Zones distribute resources across physically separate datacenters within a region.',why:'They provide high availability against datacenter failures while keeping latency low.',analogy:'Like having backup offices in different buildings in the same city so one building fire does not stop business.',hindi:'Availability Zone different physical datacenters mein resources distribute karte hain. High availability ensure karte hain.',terraform:'zones parameter in resource definitions',example:'resource "azurerm_public_ip" "main" { zones = ["1", "2", "3"] }',practices:'Deploy critical resources across zones, use zone-redundant services, plan for latency.',mistakes:'Not using zones for critical services, deploying all in single zone.',production:'Zone-redundant deployment for critical services, separate resources across 2-3 zones.',learnUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/availability-zones/az-overview',terraformUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/availability-zones/az-overview',youtubeUrl:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=azure+availability+zones',githubUrl:'https://github.com/search?q=azure+availability+zones+terraform',docsUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/availability-zones/'},
    {id:'managed-disk',title:'Managed Disk',tag:'Storage',summary:'Azure-managed block storage for virtual machines.',definition:'Managed Disk is Azure-managed block storage that simplifies VM disk management with automatic redundancy.',what:'Managed Disk provides block storage for VMs with built-in replication and disaster recovery.',why:'It eliminates storage account management, provides automatic backups, supports disk encryption.',analogy:'Like buying a hard drive that automatically makes backups and handles all maintenance.',hindi:'Managed Disk VM ke liye block storage provide karta hai. Automatic redundancy aur encryption built-in hote hain.',terraform:'azurerm_managed_disk',example:'resource "azurerm_managed_disk" "main" { name = "md-prod" storage_account_type = "Premium_LRS" }',practices:'Use Premium tier for production, enable encryption, enable snapshots.',mistakes:'Using Standard tier for databases, not enabling encryption.',production:'Premium SSD, encryption enabled, snapshots for backup strategy.',learnUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machines/managed-disks-overview',terraformUrl:'https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/azurerm/latest/docs/resources/managed_disk',youtubeUrl:'https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=azure+managed+disk',githubUrl:'https://github.com/search?q=azure+managed+disk+terraform',docsUrl:'https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machines/managed-disks-overview'}
